#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:0
#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:9
msgid "Building and running Docker images"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:0
msgid "Docker, containers, Nix, reproducible, build, tutorial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:11
msgid ""
"[Docker](https://www.docker.com/) is a set of tools and services used to "
"build, manage and deploy containers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:13
msgid ""
"As many cloud platforms offer Docker-based container hosting services, "
"creating Docker containers for a given service is a common task when "
"building reproducible software. In this tutorial, you will learn how to "
"build Docker containers using Nix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:16
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:18
msgid ""
"You will need both Nix and [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/) "
"installed. Docker is available in `nixpkgs`, which is the preferred way to "
"install it on NixOS. However, you can also use the native Docker "
"installation of your OS, if you are on another Linux distribution or macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:22
msgid "Build your first container"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:24
msgid ""
"[Nixpkgs](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs) provides `dockerTools` to create "
"Docker images:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:26
msgid ""
"{ pkgs ? import <nixpkgs> { }\n"
", pkgsLinux ? import <nixpkgs> { system = \"x86_64-linux\"; }\n"
"}:\n"
"\n"
"pkgs.dockerTools.buildImage {\n"
"  name = \"hello-docker\";\n"
"  config = {\n"
"    Cmd = [ \"${pkgsLinux.hello}/bin/hello\" ];\n"
"  };\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:40
msgid ""
"If you're running **macOS** or any platform other than `x86_64-linux`, "
"you'll need to either:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:42
msgid ""
"[Set up a remote build machine](distributed-build-setup-tutorial) to build "
"on Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:43
msgid ""
"[Cross compile to Linux](cross-compilation) by replacing `pkgsLinux.hello` "
"with `pkgs.pkgsCross.musl64.hello`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:46
msgid "We call the `dockerTools.buildImage` and pass in some parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:48
msgid "a `name` for our image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:49
msgid ""
"the `config` including the command `Cmd` that should be run inside the "
"container once the image is started. Here we reference the GNU hello package "
"from `nixpkgs` and run its executable in the container."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:53
msgid "Save this in `hello-docker.nix` and build it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:55
msgid ""
"$ nix-build hello-docker.nix\n"
"these derivations will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/qpgdp0qpd8ddi1ld72w02zkmm7n87b92-docker-layer-hello-docker.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/m4xyfyviwbi38sfplq3xx54j6k7mccfb-runtime-deps.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/v0bvy9qxa79izc7s03fhpq5nqs2h4sr5-docker-image-hello-docker.tar."
"gz.drv\n"
"warning: unknown setting 'experimental-features'\n"
"building '/nix/store/qpgdp0qpd8ddi1ld72w02zkmm7n87b92-docker-layer-hello-"
"docker.drv'...\n"
"No contents to add to layer.\n"
"Packing layer...\n"
"Computing layer checksum...\n"
"Finished building layer 'hello-docker'\n"
"building '/nix/store/m4xyfyviwbi38sfplq3xx54j6k7mccfb-runtime-deps.drv'...\n"
"building '/nix/store/v0bvy9qxa79izc7s03fhpq5nqs2h4sr5-docker-image-hello-"
"docker.tar.gz.drv'...\n"
"Adding layer...\n"
"tar: Removing leading `/' from member names\n"
"Adding meta...\n"
"Cooking the image...\n"
"Finished.\n"
"/nix/store/y74sb4nrhxr975xs7h83izgm8z75x5fc-docker-image-hello-docker.tar."
"gz\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:77
msgid ""
"The image tag (`y74sb4nrhxr975xs7h83izgm8z75x5fc`) refers to the Nix build "
"hash and makes sure that the Docker image corresponds to our Nix build. The "
"store path in the last line of the output references the Docker image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:80
msgid "Run the container"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:82
msgid ""
"To work with the container, load this image into Docker's image registry "
"from the default `result` symlink created by `nix-build`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:84
msgid ""
"$ docker load < result\n"
"Loaded image: hello-docker:y74sb4nrhxr975xs7h83izgm8z75x5fc\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:89
msgid ""
"You can also use the store path to load the image in order to avoid "
"depending on the presence of `result`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:91
msgid ""
"$ docker load < /nix/store/y74sb4nrhxr975xs7h83izgm8z75x5fc-docker-image-"
"hello-docker.tar.gz\n"
"Loaded image: hello-docker:y74sb4nrhxr975xs7h83izgm8z75x5fc\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:96
msgid ""
"Even more conveniently, you can do everything in one command. The advantage "
"of this approach is that `nix-build` will rebuild the image if there are any "
"changes and pass the new store path to `docker load`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:99
msgid ""
"$ docker load < $(nix-build hello-docker.nix)\n"
"Loaded image: hello-docker:y74sb4nrhxr975xs7h83izgm8z75x5fc\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:104
msgid "Now that you have loaded the image into Docker, you can run it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:106
msgid ""
"$ docker run -t hello-docker:y74sb4nrhxr975xs7h83izgm8z75x5fc\n"
"Hello, world!\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:111
msgid "Working with Docker images"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:113
msgid ""
"A general introduction to working with Docker images is not part of this "
"tutorial. The [official Docker documentation](https://docs.docker.com/) is a "
"much better place for that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:116
msgid ""
"Note that when you build your Docker images with Nix, you will probably not "
"write a `Dockerfile` as Nix replaces the Dockerfile functionality within the "
"Docker ecosystem. Nonetheless, understanding the anatomy of a Dockerfile may "
"still be useful to understand how Nix replaces each of its functions. Using "
"the Docker CLI, Docker Compose, Docker Swarm or Docker Hub on the other hand "
"may still be relevant, depending on your use case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:120
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:122
msgid ""
"More details on how to use `dockerTools` can be found in the [reference "
"documentation](https://nixos.org/nixpkgs/manual/#sec-pkgs-dockerTools)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:123
msgid ""
"You might like to browse through more [examples of Docker images built with "
"Nix](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/build-support/docker/"
"examples.nix)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/building-and-running-docker-images.md:124
msgid ""
"Take a look at [Arion](https://docs.hercules-ci.com/arion/), a `docker-"
"compose` wrapper with first-class support for Nix."
msgstr ""

